1.title: COOKIE WEICHE (3/4): Persist query parameters if found and no basket freeze
1.notes: Persist the APID parameter for the duration of the session - can be used to fire attributed conversions, and respects 'basket freeze' functionality.

3.notes:
Set a session-level 'basket freeze' boolean as a cookie - when the user has interacted with the basket, it's considered too late to have the attribution change.
--
Concretely, this is intended to stop users who search for a voucher code (and click and affiliate link with the voucher) from 'stealing' the attribution from the source that prompted the user's decision to buy.
